article.headline: Gardner-Webb 61, Lipscomb 55
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. (AP) -- Chris Gash scored 16 points to push Gardner-Webb to a 61-55 victory over Lipscomb on Thursday night. Thomas Sanders added 14 points and 12 rebounds for the Bulldogs (5-13, 3-4 ASC) and held the Atlantic Sun Conference's player of the year Eddie Ard to just 2-for-13 shooting. Gardner-Webb, which played without two starters while four other players battled flu symptoms, kept a slow pace that caught Lipscomb (11-8, 5-3 ASC) off-guard.. The Bison hit just 1-for-22 from beyond the arc and only 29.8 percent overall for the game. Gardner-Webb led 28-23 at the break. Trey Williams scored a game-high 21 points for the Bison, while Brian Fisk added 14.
